-- West Ham Signs Midfielder Mark Noble to New Three-Year Contract
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-09-25T19:07:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-25/west-ham-signs-midfielder-mark-noble-to-new-three-year-contract.html
West Ham signed midfielder Mark
Noble to a new three-year contract, the Premier League club said
on its website.  The agreement includes an option for a further two years,
West Ham said, without disclosing financial details.  Noble, 25, has scored 26 goals in 224 appearances for West
Ham. Now in his eighth season, he’s the east London club’s
longest-serving player.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  